::: aim

The Node-RED basics.

:::

### Steps

The following steps are explained here:

<a class='rev-view-button' href='#' onclick='return sliderTo(400);'>Step 1</a>: Adding two to an input of two, `2 + 2 = 4`. An <a class="ahl-node-only" data-ids="80f37ae872b2f29e">inject node</a> prepares the payload of 2 which flows to a <a class="ahl-node-only" data-ids="39c903d9ad714d5d">function node</a> that adds 2 to the payload that enters the node. A <a class="ahl-node-only" data-ids="965dbb28855d5d69">debug node</a> displays the final result.

<a class='rev-view-button' href='#' onclick='return sliderTo(300);'>Step 2</a>: Reusing data to compute `4 + 5 = 9`. A <a class="ahl-node-only" data-ids="6ab5f9b915b5f52e">function node adds 5</a> to the payload that enters it.

<a class='rev-view-button' href='#' onclick='return sliderTo(200);'>Step 3</a>: Execute *some* time not at the *same* time, using join to combine data, to compute `9 * 4 = 36`.

<a class='rev-view-button' href='#' onclick='return sliderTo(100);'>Step 4</a>: Reuse by copy and paste, `36 + 5 = 41`, the `+ 5` function was copied and pased

<a class='rev-view-button' href='#' onclick='return sliderTo(0);'>Step 5</a>: Reuse by using link nodes, <a class="ahl-link-node" data-ids="ba6fcd9ca7edb9f5,3740a092fc867dc8,9484f0c1c5ddcdf9">`+ 5` node</a> is called via <a class="ahl-node-only" data-ids="3fb5d5665435c419,425ecd876d73f406">link call node</a>



